PN,38503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F385A1778613066
OL,3,CGuernsey's Bailiff to retire this
OL,4,Csummer after 6 years of service
OL,6,FHaving attended school in England, Sir
OL,7,FRichard McMahon studied law in London
OL,8,Fand France before being called to the
OL,9,FEnglish Bar in 1986.
OL,11,FHe became a Guernsey Advocate in 1998
OL,12,Fbefore serving as Crown Advocate,
OL,13,FSolicitor General, Queen's Counsel and
OL,14,FDeputy Bailiff in 2012.
OL,16,FSir Richard was knighted in the King's
OL,17,FBirthday Honours list of 2023, for
OL,18,Fservices to the Crown and community in
OL,19,Fthe Bailiwick of Guernsey.
OL,21,FKey moments
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/6
